The paper deals with the communication complexity problem of a multiparty equality function in a network setting, which involves distributed computing and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of point-to-point communication links, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also introduces techniques to reduce the space of protocols, which involves information theory and coding, falling under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with the study of communication complexity, which falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a synchronous fully connected network, which involves the study of network dynamics and synchronization, falling under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
